      "title": "Structural tier classifier misclassifies cross-cutting infrastructure as CONSUMER",
      "description": "CEU-EXTRAS was classified as CONSUMER tier by the structural CEU derivation pipeline, but architecture documentation reveals it provides cross-cutting infrastructure that all domain apps depend on. Import direction alone is insufficient for tier classification of cross-cutting infrastructure components.",
      "impact": "TIER_RECLASSIFICATION",
      "severity": "MEDIUM",
      "enrichment_guidance": "Future CEU derivation should consider: (1) whether an app provides model feature mixins consumed by other apps, (2) whether an app hosts application-wide registries, (3) whether external documentation classifies it as infrastructure vs domain. Import direction analysis should be supplemented by inheritance provision analysis for cross-cutting apps.",
      "evidence_refs": ["EV-PHASE7-001", "EV-PHASE7-002", "EV-PHASE7-003"],
      "propagation_target": "CEU_DERIVATION_PIPELINE",
